 skins and BB cask.  Some of the time I spent busting trains, but most of the time was wasted running gnolls down due to my encumbered state.  I was fortunate, and had an hour in the morning,  first thing I saw was the master brewer.  Good now all I need is a few more skins, I bought one and found one the night before. <BR>  <BR> I was getting sick of auctioning and at best getting no response, and at worst finding out someone had a pelt.  I did a shout &quot;I hate this place, it smells like wet dog.  If i don't get my last skin soon I'm gonna make the biggest train in recent memory!&quot;  Shortly after, I found an elite gnoll,  dead.  I think it was one that I helped kill, the gnollslayer was in over his head and beyond my ability to save.  Finally I get the last skin. <BR>  <BR> Now, its time to have some real fun.  Shout,&quot;Train to Halas.  It'll be a bit,  I want to do it right!&quot;  I was in the elite 5 area, and it wasn't too tough to find a few gnolls, too bad the elites were all dead.  I run in a little deaper, through a door.  OK,  5 thats a good start.  get them aggro on me, then start running up. Attack, backstab, disarm...  anything to make them attack me.  I ran through the snake pit, then around so I was underneath the elite ledge.  Finally I make it to the bridge and see a bunch of people fighting.  If they are smart they won't touch my train..   I get to the top,  what?  only 3. <BR>  <BR> I hear, &quot;Gawayne just killed me.&quot;  Sorry bud,  slice and dice time.  As I'm slaughtering these pathetic creatures I see my factions skyrocket.  Someone down there must have a good group.  More slowly work their way up to me,  I think about 8 total. <BR>  <BR> I must say, I am impressed with the group down below,  I estimate I had about 15-20 on me at the peak of the train, and I only killed about half up top.  To those of you who died,  I'm sorry, but I needed some stress relief, and we all know blackburrow is not a very safe place. <BR>  <BR> On a side note,  Gnoll fangs killed my faction with Circle of Unseen Hands, and elite gnolls are still decent money.  Not the greatest though,  no exp. <BR>  <BR> Gawayne <BR> 27th Xegony <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/ugrimjawbadflagon.showPublicProfile>Grimjaw Badflagon</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/00 9:11:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blackburrow</span><hr size=1> Man....jeesh whats up with THAT... <BR>  <BR>  <p>Grimjaw Badflagon
Barbarian Rogue
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/ugyorg.showPublicProfile>Gyorg</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/00 2:42:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Gawayne, just causing trouble</span><hr size=1> So thats what you were doing before I met up w/ you in Sol A.  Just causing trouble all over they place.  Trying to instill doubt in the goblins.  You were lucky to make it out.  Next time your in Lynada room, run for Sol B, not Lavastorm ).  Anyway, I'm glad you got the purse, hope I roll better next time.  See you at Ortalius <BR>  <BR> Gyorg Rogue of the 18th moon over Xegony <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nox>Nox</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/23/00 2:29:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gawayne, just causing trouble</span><hr size=1> I hope yer not braggin' about this, mate.<br>
