 <p>Fiae Soulmender "The Machine" <br>
45 Rogue Veeshan (Warden)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/upoisin.showPublicProfile>Poisin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/28/00 12:44:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blackburrow</span><hr size=1> I think we all have silently wished to take frustrations out on other players.  It is wrong, and we know it, but it does work. hee hee<br>
<br>
If you have ever the desire to do something like this, nothing compares to a death train in Unrest.  I know many of you know exactly what I am talking about.  In no ither zone have I seen a literal &quot;trail&quot; of dead bodies from the porch to zone.<br>
<br>
This is where I make my train of death, cause if you are going to be a jerk, you may as well do it right.  Mind you, this is in the wee hours when there is 15 people in the zone.  Several ample warnings are shouted and even had 8-9 line up near the fountains to see if I can make it out.  Got a sow from a kindly druid and proceeded to clear the knight room, bar room, the back, the fireplace, the savant, and the basement.  <br>
<br>
Wonderful thing a cleric can be. Divine barrier and aura enabled me to get out of the basement unmolested by those skels, tentacles, ghouls, fungus, bats and hags. I was quite amazed at how many residents are actually in unrest.<br>
<br>
Needless to say, one person got too close to the backwash on the returning train and subsequently died.  I ressed him, and then powered back the exp he lost.  Handed out lvl 44 buffs and healed the odd person.<br>
<br>
All in all, it really helped get my frustrations out and even livened up the zone for a while.  But it is bad, it is wrong- don't do this unless you can compensate properly for all the trouble it causes.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.showMessage?topicID=202.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.showMessage?topicID=238.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.emailToFriend?topicID=225.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.threadControl?topicID=225.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=225.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=225.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Training Studio<option value="thesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers">The Back Alley<opti